<p>Think of your biggest competitor. Now think about outranking them. Doesn’t seem as hard now, huh?<br></p>



<p class="has-sleek-light-grey-background-color has-background"><strong>Action item:</strong> Build links from best-of content. Bonus if you build them to uber-competitive product pages. Who knows, you might just outrank Amazon.</p>



<h2 id="Activate-New-Subscribers-with-Small-Wins"><strong>7. Activate New Subscribers with Small Wins</strong></h2>



<p>Not everyone is ready to buy from you.<br></p>



<p>That’s a given.<br></p>



<p>I know that. You know that. And MeUndies certainly know that (judging from their remarketing.)<br></p>



<p>But that doesn’t mean you can’t pitch <em>something </em>in your onboarding emails.<br></p>



<p>Take a recent experience as an example.<br></p>



<p>After I joined their newsletter, but before I became a customer, I got an email with the subject line “7 Million Happy Butts and Going Strong.” In it, was an invite to join the “MeUndies Fam” by following MeUndies on social media.<br></p>



<p>Here’s an excerpt:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="638" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email-1024x638.png" alt="MeUndies Small Win Email" class="wp-image-75614" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email-1024x638.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email-300x187.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email-768x478.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email-380x237.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email-600x374.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email-760x473.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email-56x35.png 56w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email-80x50.png 80w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email-740x461.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email-220x137.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email-385x240.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Small-Win-Email.png 1325w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>There’s a good reason for sending an <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/free-email-list" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">email</a> like the above:<br></p>



<p><em>It’s a great way to activate new subscribers.</em><br></p>



<p>Why?<br></p>



<p><em>Because</em> <em>people tend to behave in ways that are consistent with an earlier action.</em><br></p>



<p>In other words, <strong>when someone complies with a small request—like following a social media profile—they’re more likely to comply with a similar or larger request later (like buying something).</strong><br></p>



<p>This is known as <em><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/commitment-and-consistency-examples" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">commitment and consistency</a></em>&#8230;&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>&#8230;and it’s one of the best persuasion triggers in marketing.<br></p>



<p>Granted, it won’t guarantee more customers, but it won’t hurt your chances, either.<br></p>



<p class="has-sleek-light-grey-background-color has-background"><strong>Action item.</strong> Activate new subscribers by inviting them to something other than buying something. Ask yourself, “What’s a small request I can make?” Then, ask them to do it.</p>



<h2 id="Persuasion-Triggers-+-Cart-Recovery-Emails-=-More-Sales"><strong>8. Persuasion Triggers + Cart Recovery Emails = More Sales</strong></h2>



<p>If you’re an e-tailer, you know the importance of sending cart recovery emails.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>I won’t repeat anything you already know here.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>But what I will do, is show you a clever way MeUndies are using <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/email-subject-lines">persuasion triggers</a> in their cart recovery emails.<br></p>



<p>For example, while writing this post, I abandoned my cart. And a few hours later, I got a cart recovery email.&nbsp;<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="739" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2-1024x739.png" alt="MeUndies Cart Recovery Email 2" class="wp-image-75506" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2-1024x739.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2-300x216.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2-768x554.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2-380x274.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2-600x433.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2-760x548.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2-49x35.png 49w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2-69x50.png 69w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2-679x490.png 679w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2-220x159.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2-385x278.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-2.png 1275w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Nothing new there. We all know scarcity is the bedrock of <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-email-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">e-commerce email marketing</a>.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>But here’s where they differentiate themselves&#8230;&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>A day later, I got another email, only this time, MeUndies informed me that my cart had expired:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="731" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-1024x731.png" alt="MeUndies Cart Recovery Email" class="wp-image-75514" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-1024x731.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-300x214.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-768x548.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-380x271.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-600x428.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-760x542.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-49x35.png 49w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-70x50.png 70w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-687x490.png 687w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-220x157.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email-385x275.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email.png 1275w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>In two emails, I went from fear of missing out (“Your favorites won’t be around forever”) to ACTUALLY missing out (“Your cart has expired”).<br></p>



<p>Of course, I hadn’t really missed out—my item was still available. But I FELT like I had. And clicking “Get My Items Back” was enough to give me the extra nudge I need to buy. (Yes, like many shoppers, I’m a sucker for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loss_aversion" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">loss aversion</a>.)<br></p>



<p>Another trigger MeUndies take is incentivizing order completion with a coupon. In other words, triggering <em>implied urgency</em>.<br></p>



<p>After abandoning my cart, on another occasion, I got the following email:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="639" height="460" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email1.png" alt="MeUndies Cart Recovery Email(1)" class="wp-image-75510" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email1.png 639w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email1-300x216.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email1-380x274.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email1-600x432.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email1-49x35.png 49w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email1-69x50.png 69w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email1-220x158.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Cart-Recovery-Email1-385x277.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 100vw, 639px" /></figure></div>



<p>Everyone loves discounts. And if it’s for an item you showed interest in, and the coupon is a surprise, it, too, can be enough to convert on-the-fence buyers.<br></p>



<p>And if that wasn’t enough, they also linked to similar products, in case I changed your mind since you last shopped.<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="696" height="346" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Unisex-Onesies.png" alt="Unisex Onesies" class="wp-image-75662" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Unisex-Onesies.png 696w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Unisex-Onesies-300x149.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Unisex-Onesies-380x189.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Unisex-Onesies-600x298.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Unisex-Onesies-70x35.png 70w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Unisex-Onesies-101x50.png 101w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Unisex-Onesies-220x109.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Unisex-Onesies-385x191.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 696px) 100vw, 696px" /></figure></div>



<p>It’s the little things that make a big difference. Don’t overlook them.<br></p>



<p class="has-sleek-light-grey-background-color has-background"><strong>Action item:</strong> It’s not enough to remind shoppers what they’ve left in their cart; you need to remind them what they’ll LOSE (even if it’s time needing to re-add their items). Tell dawdling buyers what they’re about to LOSE. Then, what they’ve LOST, before telling them how to get their items back. Targeting consumer psychology goes a long way.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<h2 id="Ask-for-Feedback-to-Improve-Your-Product"><strong>9. Ask for Feedback to Improve Your Product</strong></h2>



<p>You know the importance of <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/customer-feedback" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">asking for feedback</a>. With the right data, you can do more of what works and ruthlessly eliminate what doesn’t.<br></p>



<p>But are you asking the right questions at the right time?<br></p>



<p>While writing this article, I became a MeUndies customer. And a few days after my order arrived, I got the following email.<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="700" height="410" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Customer-Survey-Email.png" alt="MeUndies Customer Survey Email" class="wp-image-75518" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Customer-Survey-Email.png 700w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Customer-Survey-Email-300x176.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Customer-Survey-Email-380x223.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Customer-Survey-Email-600x351.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Customer-Survey-Email-60x35.png 60w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Customer-Survey-Email-85x50.png 85w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Customer-Survey-Email-220x129.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Customer-Survey-Email-385x226.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></figure></div>



<p>When I clicked the link, MeUndies redirected me to a survey asking me about my experience:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="387" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email-1024x387.png" alt="MeUndies Feedback Email" class="wp-image-75546" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email-1024x387.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email-300x113.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email-768x290.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email-380x144.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email-600x227.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email-760x287.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email-93x35.png 93w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email-132x50.png 132w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email-740x280.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email-220x83.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email-385x146.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Feedback-Email.png 1190w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>They asked me the usual questions you would expect from a survey—my age, my gender, my ethnicity, etc.<br></p>



<p>But, like any good survey, they also vary their questions depending on what you bought.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>For instance, if you bought an item for someone else, you bypass questions like the one below:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="471" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2-1024x471.png" alt="MeUndies Survey Question 2" class="wp-image-75618" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2-1024x471.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2-300x138.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2-768x353.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2-380x175.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2-600x276.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2-760x350.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2-76x35.png 76w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2-109x50.png 109w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2-740x341.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2-220x101.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2-385x177.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question-2.png 1195w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Asking closed questions offers MeUndies more specific answers—giving them more quantitative and qualitative data to improve their product line.<br></p>



<p>Here’s a great example of one question doing that:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="516" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1-1024x516.png" alt="MeUndies Survey Question(1)" class="wp-image-75622" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1-1024x516.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1-300x151.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1-768x387.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1-380x192.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1-600x303.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1-760x383.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1-69x35.png 69w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1-99x50.png 99w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1-740x373.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1-220x111.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1-385x194.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Survey-Question1.png 1190w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Interestingly, a week later, I got another email asking how strongly I would recommend a friend.</p>







<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="820" height="590" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Net-Promoter-Score.png" alt="MeUndies Net Promoter Score" class="wp-image-75582" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Net-Promoter-Score.png 820w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Net-Promoter-Score-300x216.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Net-Promoter-Score-768x553.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Net-Promoter-Score-380x273.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Net-Promoter-Score-600x432.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Net-Promoter-Score-760x547.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Net-Promoter-Score-49x35.png 49w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Net-Promoter-Score-69x50.png 69w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Net-Promoter-Score-681x490.png 681w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Net-Promoter-Score-220x158.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MeUndies-Net-Promoter-Score-385x277.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px" /></figure></div>



<p>“Why would they send another email asking for feedback?”<br></p>



<p>I thought that, too.<br></p>



<p>And I pondered on it. A LOT.<br></p>



<p>That is until I looked further, and assume it’s to improve their net promoter score.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>You see, in the previous email, they survey customers using SurveyMonkey. It’s important information, but it’s hard to extrapolate from the rest of the data. But in the above email, they use a software called <a href="https://delighted.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Delighted</a>, giving them immediate feedback in one place:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="491" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-1024x491.png" alt="Delighted" class="wp-image-75446" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-1024x491.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-300x144.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-768x368.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-1536x736.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-380x182.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-600x288.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-760x364.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-1440x690.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-73x35.png 73w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-104x50.png 104w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-740x355.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-220x105.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted-385x185.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Delighted.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Of course, it’s also an opportunity to reach out again to customers that didn’t take or even complete the survey, giving them the feedback they need to improve their product.<br></p>



<p class="has-sleek-light-grey-background-color has-background"><strong>Action item:</strong> Ask customers for feedback. Then, reach out once more with the single most important question. Not everyone will complete the first, but if the follow up is easier to complete, it’s more likely you’ll get responses.&nbsp;</p>



<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


