										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<h1 class="has-text-align-center"><strong>E-Commerce SEO: How to Outrank Your Competitors (2021)</strong></h1>
<div class="post-content-category"><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/category/growth-marketing" rel="category tag">Growth Marketing</a></div>


<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-large"><img width="1024" height="240" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-1024x240.jpg" alt="E-Commerce SEO (WordPress)" class="wp-image-73756" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-1024x240.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-300x70.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-768x180.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-1536x360.jpg 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-2048x480.jpg 2048w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-380x89.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-600x141.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-760x178.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-1440x338.jpg 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-149x35.jpg 149w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-213x50.jpg 213w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-740x173.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-220x52.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E-Commerce-SEO-Wordpress-385x90.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>


<div id="preamble-block_5e721c26c3386" class="block-preamble"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">E-commerce has been experiencing steady growth between 2008 and 2017. </span></p>
</div>






<p>As of Q3 2017, it accounted for <a href="https://www.census.gov/retail/mrts/www/data/pdf/ec_current.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">8.4 percent </a>of total retail sales at $107 billion, which isn’t too shabby.<br></p>



<p>So there is plenty of opportunities.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>Being successful largely boils down to gaining visibility and getting your e-commerce site in front of your target audience.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>And what’s the best way to gain visibility and drive a high volume of qualified leads to your store?&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>Two words: search traffic.<br></p>



<p>According to <a href="https://www.wolfgangdigital.com/uploads/general/eComKPI2016-Public2.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Wolfgang Digital</a>, “43 percent of e-commerce traffic comes from Google search.”<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="460" height="372" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/3-Percent-of-E-Commerce-Traffic-Comes-from-Google-Search-1.png" alt="3 Percent of E-Commerce Traffic Comes from Google Search" class="wp-image-73724" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/3-Percent-of-E-Commerce-Traffic-Comes-from-Google-Search-1.png 460w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/3-Percent-of-E-Commerce-Traffic-Comes-from-Google-Search-1-300x243.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/3-Percent-of-E-Commerce-Traffic-Comes-from-Google-Search-1-380x307.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/3-Percent-of-E-Commerce-Traffic-Comes-from-Google-Search-1-43x35.png 43w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/3-Percent-of-E-Commerce-Traffic-Comes-from-Google-Search-1-62x50.png 62w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/3-Percent-of-E-Commerce-Traffic-Comes-from-Google-Search-1-220x178.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/3-Percent-of-E-Commerce-Traffic-Comes-from-Google-Search-1-385x311.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 460px) 100vw, 460px" /></figure></div>



<p>So it’s clear that e-commerce SEO should be your top priority.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>Nailing the key elements and covering all of your bases should help catapult your online store to the top of the rankings.<br></p>



<p>And luckily, outranking most of your competitors shouldn’t be all that difficult.<br></p>



<p>While SEO, in general, has become incredibly sophisticated, you could argue that the SEO for many e-commerce sites is pretty lackluster.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>It’s all about following the right formula and putting in the time.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>With that being said, here’s a guide on the fundamentals of e-commerce SEO and the steps you need to take to outrank your competitors.<br></p>



<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<div id="contentupgrade-block_5e6f42148dc97" class="block-content-upgrade">
    <div class="text">
        <p class="text-pretitle">FREE DOWNLOADABLE BONUS</p>
        <h2 class="text-title">Want More Growth Marketing Strategies?</h2>
        <div class="text-content"><p>Get access to our free growth marketing toolkit and skyrocket your website traffic today (includes resources not found in the blog post).</p>
</div>
